post: {'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs will help treat addicts. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalized, the prison system would be less over-crowded, which is a [significant issue](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2019.html) in the US.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalisation of cigarettes [did not stop](https://thedebrief.co.uk/news/real-life/1-every-7-british-cigarettes-contraband-counterfeit/) illicit and poor quality cheaper versions. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Marijuana use in the Netherlands has [not increased](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) following decriminalisation; in fact, cannabis consumption is lower compared to countries with stricter legislation such as the UK.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various governments have already facilitated access to drugs and positive outcomes have come of this.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Children of drug addicts would have a much higher chance of receiving the appropriate help if drug users did not have to hide.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Rational discussion of the costs and benefits of smoking tobacco and negative ads led a lot of people to decide it isn't worth doing. All without prohibiting it."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Prohibition does not treat addicts, treatment, and prevention of addiction do. Both of these are accomplished far more effectively without the threat of incarceration for merely admitting use. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2014, [8.7%](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-healthcare-costs-smoking-idUSKBN0JX2BE20141219) of all healthcare spending in the US was spent on tobacco-related illnesses.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug prohibition might be inspired by some kind of racism but abandoning it would not necessarily mean an improvement of the situation for those incarcerated or addicted to drugs. There are still many other systematic racial issues unrelated to drug prohibition.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If government regulations lead to drugs being expensive, it is possible people will still try to access cheaper drugs on a black market and these drugs may still be dangerous or of poor quality. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addiction treatment isn't actually very expensive or costly, and is likely to be clinically simpler to resolve than is widely assumed."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs may also alter the strength of which learning \\(permanent changes of neural activity\\) reacts to such rewards.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would enable people to easily manage their own pain medication themselves without the trials and tribulations of doctors and presciptions and all those agonizing hoops you need to jump through along the way.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The risk of MDMA is not higher than many sports. MDMA has been compared to [horseback riding](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk/7876425.stm) in terms of risks. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Dangerous substitute drugs will be contained. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As this is also true under prohibition, it's an argument for proper education, not an argument against legalization. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation may reduce the price of drugs. This would have positive effects. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is no way to determine in advance what the additional resources/revenue will be used for by the government. It may not be earmarked for harm reduction. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalization \\(and incarceration\\) causes lasting harm to a person's health and life outcomes."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Criminals are not interested in drugs, their core interest is money. To gain the largest amount of money, in the quickest time, with the least effort, is their ultimate goal. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the same way that people sign contracts in which they voluntarily limit their freedom for a certain amount of time, a person who chooses freely to take drugs is choosing to limit their self-control freely.
